http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/bangalore/Rs.-118-crore-released-for-AMRUT-scheme/article13999261.ece

The Union government has released Rs. 118 crore to the State for implementing urban development projects under its flagship programme, Atal Mission for Rejuvenation and Urban Transformation (AMRUT), for the first phase. A total of 27 cities in the State, including Bengaluru, Dharwad, Mysuru, Belagavi and Mangaluru, have been covered under AMRUT.Minister for Urban Development Vinay Kumar Sorake told The Hindu on Wednesday that Rs. 118 crore would be spent by March 31, 2016. Provision for drinking water, underground drainage, waste disposal, transportation, and greenery would be the major focus of the scheme.All the cities/towns having population of more than a lakh have been included in the AMRUT programme, which will be implemented on PPP model with funding by the Centre and the State.Rs. 1,000 cr. for BengaluruIn Bengaluru, Rs. 1,000 crore would be spent in the next five years on providing basic infrastructure.